    "titleZh": "《百合之歌》",
    "titleEn": "Song of Lilies",
    "year": "2026",
    "medium": "Oil on Canvas（布面油画）",
    "dimensions": "60 cm（Diameter）",
    "series": "Light and Life（光与生命）",
    "category": "oil",
    "image": "assets/images/artworks-web/catalogue-raisonne/百合之歌-2000.jpg",
    "keywords": "English:Lily · Flowers · Still Life · Circular Painting · Oil Painting · Color · Light · Vitality\n中文：百合 · 花卉 · 静物 · 圆形绘画 · 油画 · 色彩 · 光 · 生命力",
    "statementZh": "《百合之歌》创作于2026年，以圆形画幅描绘盛放的百合花。金黄色背景与蓝白色花朵形成鲜明而富有张力的色彩关系，使花朵在光线中呈现饱满而自由的生命状态。圆形构图强化了画面的凝聚力，也赋予作品完整而温暖的视觉感受。作品并非追求植物学式的准确再现，而是借由富有表现力的笔触和色彩，表达生命绽放的力量。百合象征纯净、希望与新生，在浓烈的光感中成为关于生命活力与精神丰盈的视觉隐喻。",
    "statementEn": "Song of Lilies was completed in 2026. Painted on a circular canvas, the work depicts blooming lilies against a luminous golden background. The contrast between vibrant yellows and cool blue-white petals creates a dynamic visual rhythm, allowing the flowers to radiate vitality and light.Rather than pursuing botanical realism, the painting emphasizes expressive color and painterly gestures. The lilies become a metaphor for purity, renewal, and the flourishing energy of life.",
