    "artworkId": "KXW-P-042",
    "titleZh": "《绿风酸甜》",
    "titleEn": "Sweet and Sour in the Green Wind",
    "year": "2025",
    "medium": "Black-and-white Woodcut Print（黑白木刻）",
    "dimensions": "120 × 82 cm",
    "series": "Pastoral Poems（田园诗）",
    "category": "printmaking",
    "image": "assets/images/artworks-web/catalogue-raisonne/KXW-042-2000.jpg",
    "keywords": "English:Grapes · Vineyard · Harvest · Rural Life · Woodcut · Memory · Nature · Poetry中文：葡萄 · 葡萄园 · 丰收 · 乡村生活 · 木刻版画 · 自然 · 记忆 · 诗意",
    "statementZh": "《绿风酸甜》完成于2025年。作品以葡萄园为题材，描绘成熟葡萄被防虫网轻轻包裹的景象。透明的网袋既保护着果实，也记录着农人对丰收的期待。枝叶、葡萄与远处民居共同构成宁静而富有生活气息的乡村图景。黑白木刻删去了色彩，却保留了风、光与时间留下的痕迹。酸与甜不仅属于果实，也属于土地上的劳作与等待。作品希望通过版画语言，呈现田园生活质朴、真实而富有生命力的诗意。",
    "statementEn": "Completed in 2025, Sweet and Sour in the Green Wind depicts grape clusters protected by translucent bags in a rural vineyard. The coverings symbolize both care and the anticipation of harvest, while vines, leaves, and village houses evoke the quiet rhythm of country life.By removing color, the black-and-white woodcut emphasizes texture, light, and the passage of time. The 'sweet and sour' of the title refers not only to the fruit but also to the patience, labor, and hope embedded in the land.",
    "exhibitionHistory": "中文：\n• 2025 入选第十一届广东省版画作品展。\n• 展出地点：江门市新会美术馆。\n\nEnglish:",
    "awards": "",
    "collection": "",
    "publication": "中文：\n• 收录《第十一届广东省版画作品展》官方展览资料。\n\nEnglish:",
    "fullRecordText": "Artwork Record / 作品档案\nArtwork ID: KXW-P-042\nTitle (CN): 《绿风酸甜》\nTitle (EN): Sweet and Sour in the Green Wind\nYear: 2025\nMedium: Black-and-white Woodcut Print（黑白木刻）\nDimensions: 120 × 82 cm\nSeries (CN): Pastoral Poems（田园诗）\nSeries (EN): \nArtwork Statement (CN)\n《绿风酸甜》完成于2025年。作品以葡萄园为题材，描绘成熟葡萄被防虫网轻轻包裹的景象。透明的网袋既保护着果实，也记录着农人对丰收的期待。枝叶、葡萄与远处民居共同构成宁静而富有生活气息的乡村图景。黑白木刻删去了色彩，却保留了风、光与时间留下的痕迹。酸与甜不仅属于果实，也属于土地上的劳作与等待。作品希望通过版画语言，呈现田园生活质朴、真实而富有生命力的诗意。\nArtwork Statement (EN)\nCompleted in 2025, Sweet and Sour in the Green Wind depicts grape clusters protected by translucent bags in a rural vineyard. The coverings symbolize both care and the anticipation of harvest, while vines, leaves, and village houses evoke the quiet rhythm of country life.By removing color, the black-and-white woodcut emphasizes texture, light, and the passage of time. The 'sweet and sour' of the title refers not only to the fruit but also to the patience, labor, and hope embedded in the land.\nKeywords / 关键词\nEnglish:Grapes · Vineyard · Harvest · Rural Life · Woodcut · Memory · Nature · Poetry中文：葡萄 · 葡萄园 · 丰收 · 乡村生活 · 木刻版画 · 自然 · 记忆 · 诗意\nExhibition History / 展览经历\n中文：\n• 2025 入选第十一届广东省版画作品展。\n• 展出地点：江门市新会美术馆。\n\nEnglish:\nPublication / 出版发表\n中文：\n• 收录《第十一届广东省版画作品展》官方展览资料。\n\nEnglish:",
